[Z] CONSTRAINT DRIFT DETECTION — compare implementation against CLAUDE.md §16

Read CLAUDE.md "## What NOT to do" section (the 10 constraints from plan.md §16).
For each constraint, verify that the files created or modified in this task
do NOT violate it.

For each constraint:
  - PASS: no violation found in the files touched by this task
  - FAIL: violation found — describe the violation with file:line references
  - N/A: constraint is not applicable to the files touched by this task

Common drift patterns to check:
  1. Layer rule violations: did the implementation call a lower-layer class
     directly from a higher-layer module? (e.g., domain → delivery)
  2. Naming drift: did the implementation use names that contradict the
     ubiquitous language from plan.md §2?
  3. Missing correlation ID: did the implementation omit the correlation ID
     header in API responses?
  4. Test data isolation: are domain objects constructed by hand instead of
     using factory functions from plan.md §13?

For each FAIL: fix the violation immediately. Do not proceed until all
constraints are PASS or N/A.

Print: "DRIFT CHECK: [N] constraints checked, [N] PASS, [N] FAIL, [N] N/A"
